OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Fri 13 Mar to Sun 22 Mar
OL,6,FChangeable through much of this
OL,7,Fperiod, as Atlantic frontal systems
OL,8,Fpass close to or across the UK at
OL,9,Ftimes. These will bring some
OL,10,Foccasional spells of rain or showers,
OL,11,Fmost frequent in the west and
OL,12,Fnorthwest, and perhaps accompanied by
OL,13,Fstrong winds. However, there should
OL,14,Falso be some drier interludes under
OL,15,Ftransient ridges of high pressure,
OL,16,Fwith longer dry periods most likely in
OL,17,Fthe south and east, though even here
OL,18,Fsome wet weather is likely at times.
OL,19,FTemperatures will be near-average for
OL,20,Fthe period as a whole, but with some
OL,21,Fshorter-duration colder interludes at
OL,22,Ftimes when frost and hill snow will be
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fpossible. Later in the period there
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fmay be a transition to more blocked or
OL,25,Fslower evolving weather patterns,
OL,26,Fthough confidence in the detail of
